{
  "texts": [
    "In unsupervised learning, computer vision is able to recognise common features in images (cluster analysis), without annotations.",
    "Annotation is performed by assigning a label to the selected part of the image, or a single label for the entire image.",
    "Feature extraction can be included under this stage -or alternatively be seen as a separate stage in the computer vision process.",
    "A feature is defined as ''a measurable piece of data in your image that is unique to that specific object … a distinct colour or a specific shape such as a line, edge, or image segment''.",
    "55 The features can be extracted manually or automatically."
  ]
}